{
  "text": "After immobilization on Nytran filters (Schleicher and Schuell), the I-CeuI-generated fragments were hybridized with three different probes: the 16S and 23S rRNA probe (Roche Diagnostics, Meylan, France), a bla OXA-23 probe, and a probe specific to the ampC gene of E. coli. Labeling, hybridization, and revelation were performed as previously reported [CITATION_1] . The rRNA probe hybridized with the seven I-CeuI-generated fragments. The bla OXA-23 probe hybridized only with the \u03fe2.2-Mb gene to be maintained in the strain, it must therefore have been inserted in the chromosome probably by genetic events of recombination, cointegration, or transposition. To our knowledge, this is the first report of a chromosome-encoded class D enzyme in the family Enterobacteriaceae. Class A and C enzymes (GN-79 and CMY-3), which are generally plasmid encoded, have been observed in the chromosome of P. mirabilis strains [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . The putative insert sequence ISEcp-1 was observed upstream of bla CMY-3 (data not shown), but was not detected in P. mirabilis CFO239.",
